200b: The leading 3 numbers identify the breeder pair (parents)
Kinship coefficients (from 0 to 1) for hypothetical offspring that would come from the corresponding breeder parents.
These values in off-diagonals show how related two offspring that come from distinct breeder pairs are to each other.
For example, a pup that comes from Breeder Pair 216 and a pup from Breeder Pair 205 would be 54.3% related (more than full siblings).
